Testing API

werkzeug.test.EnvironBuilder

    class werkzeug.test.EnvironBuilder(
        path='/',                   errors_stream=None,
        base_url=None,              multithread=False,
        query_string=None,          multiprocess=False,
        method='GET',               run_once=False,
        input_stream=None,          headers=None,
        content_type=None,          data=None,
        content_length=None,        environ_base=None,
        environ_overrides=None,     charset='utf-8'
    )

    builder = EnvironBuilder()
    environ = builder.get_environ()

`query_string` can be an optional string or dict


this signature is also used in 
    test.create_environ()
    wrappers.BaseResponse.from_values()
    test.Client.open()


werkzeug.test.Client

    class werkzeug.test.Client(
        application,
        response_wrapper=None,
        use_cookies=True,
        allow_subdomain_redirects=False
    )


werkzeug.test.create_environ([options])
     a thin wrapper over EnvironBuilder

werkzeug.test.run_wsgi_app(app, environ, buffered=False)
    params:
        app : application to execute
        buffered : set to True to enforce buffering
    returns: tuple of the form (app_iter, status, headers) 
        
